<p>HVAC companies lose an average of 3.7 hours per employee per week to inaccurate time tracking. That's $312 weekly for a technician earning $25/hour, or $16,224 annually per employee. Manual timesheets, buddy punching, and forgotten clock-ins create payroll nightmares and kill profitability.</p>

